          You’ll start by understanding how to read a chord chart, so you know exactly where to place your fingers on the fretboard.
          From there, we’ll explore the three core chord types every beginner should know: major, minor, and dominant 7th shapes,
          all in the open position. Once you’re comfortable forming these chords, you’ll learn how to put them into practice by playing a
          simple 12-bar blues using a basic, easy-to-follow strumming pattern.
        </p>

