      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Introduction</h2>
        <p class="body-text">
          Major chords are some of the first shapes beginners learn because they sound bright, happy, and full.
          A major chord is built from three notes: the root, the major third, and the perfect fifth.
          On this page, you’ll learn the most common open-position major chords and the notes that make each one up.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- A MAJOR -->
      <section class="section">
